    "description": {
      "value": "<p>In this stance, the user takes the Champuru style to an additional level by incorporating his pure instincts to maximize the effectiveness of his choices in attacks.<br><br>All attacks in this stance are modified by dexterity. While in this form the user gains a +2 to attack and tumble checks and a +2 dodge bonus to defense against attacks of opportunity. Also, his ability to overpower an enemy is intact, as he also gains a +2 to damage and trip checks. He must still move at least 10 feet every round, if movement is halted then the stance is broken. All above modifications only apply to a user wielding a sword.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> Champuru (f), Taijutsu Adept (f), Taijutsu 9 ranks, Tumble 9 ranks</p>\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> The third step in mastery of this technique allows the user to feint as a movement action.</p>\n",
